9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 105, L.D. 172, “An Act to Require the
10 Maine State Police to Create a Statewide List of Missing Persons”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Require the Maine State Police to Create a Statewide List of Missing
13 Persons and Study Improvements for Investigating Missing Persons Cases'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §1512 is enacted to read:
17 §1512. Missing persons list
18 In cooperation with appropriate law enforcement agencies, the Bureau of State Police
19 shall establish by December 31, 2026 and maintain a publicly accessible website that lists
20 all open missing persons cases in the State. The website must contain details regarding each
21 missing person in the State that include, but are not limited to, the missing person's
22 demographics, photograph, circumstances of disappearance and last known location and
23 any additional information that may help in locating or identifying the missing person. The
24 website must be updated, at a minimum, once every month to include any new missing
25 person's information as required by this section.
26 Sec. 2. Department of Public Safety, Bureau of State Police to convene
27 working group. The Department of Public Safety, Bureau of State Police shall convene
28 a working group to review best practices for investigating missing persons cases in the
29 State, determining the feasibility of implementing those best practices in a training module
30 in the Maine Criminal Justice Academy's curriculum, reviewing the effectiveness of the
31 Silver Alert Program under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 25, section 2202 and
32 identifying ways to improve the Silver Alert Program. The working group must include the
33 following members:
34 1. The Commissioner of Public Safety, or the commissioner's designee;
35 2. The Chief of the State Police, or the chief's designee;
