COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 105, L.D. 172
1 3. The Chief Medical Examiner, or the chief's designee;
2 4. A representative from the Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife, Bureau of
3 Warden Service;
4 5. The Director of the Maine Criminal Justice Academy, or the director's designee;
5 6. A representative from a statewide association representing sheriffs;
6 7. A representative from a statewide association representing chiefs of police;
7 8. A representative from a statewide volunteer association specializing in search and
8 rescue;
9 9. A representative from an organization that specializes in maintaining a missing
10 persons list; and
11 10. A family member of a missing person.
12 By December 3, 2025, the bureau shall submit a report that includes the findings and
13 recommendations of the working group, including suggested legislation, for presentation
14 to the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety. The committee
15 may submit legislation based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd
16 Legislature.
17 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
18 allocations are made.
