35 SUMMARY
3366 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. It requires the Department of
3377 Public Safety, Bureau of State Police to establish and maintain a publicly accessible website
3388 that lists all open missing persons cases in the State. The website must be updated, at a
3399 minimum, once every month to include any new missing person's information. It also
Page 2 - 132LR0397(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 105, L.D. 172
410 directs the bureau to convene a working group to review best practices for investigating
421 missing persons cases, determining the feasibility of implementing those best practices in
432 the Maine Criminal Justice Academy's curriculum, reviewing the effectiveness of the Silver
443 Alert Program and identifying ways to improve the program. The bureau is required to
454 submit a report by December 3, 2025 to the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice
465 and Public Safety, which may submit legislation to the Second Regular Session of the
476 132nd Legislature. The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
